# Bandit Level 19 â†’ Level 20

## Level Goal
Menemukan password untuk level selanjutnya menggunakan setuid binary yang ada di home directory untuk mengakses file password di /etc/bandit_pass.

## Detailed Command Breakdown

### 1. SSH Connection
```bash
ssh bandit19@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220
```

### 2. Setuid Binary Usage
```bash
# Check file permissions
ls -l bandit20-do

# Execute as different user
./bandit20-do cat /etc/bandit_pass/bandit20

# Check file type
file bandit20-do
```

## Setuid Binaries

### 1. Permission Management
```bash
# View permissions
ls -l file
stat file

# Set SUID bit
chmod u+s file
chmod 4755 file

# Remove SUID
chmod u-s file
chmod 0755 file
```

### 2. Process Execution
```bash
# Execute as owner
./suid_binary

# Execute with arguments
./suid_binary arg1 arg2

# Execute with environment
env VAR=value ./suid_binary
```

### 3. Security Context
```bash
# Check process owner
ps -ef | grep process

# Check capabilities
getcap file
setcap cap_name+ep file

# Check security context
ls -Z file
ps -Z
```

## Process Management

### 1. Process Information
```bash
# List processes
ps aux
ps -ef

# Process tree
pstree
ps auxf

# Process details
top
htop
```

### 2. Process Control
```bash
# Send signals
kill PID
killall process_name

# Priority control
nice -n 10 command
renice 10 PID

# Resource limits
ulimit -a
```

### 3. Process Monitoring
```bash
# System activity
vmstat
iostat
sar

# Process tracking
strace command
ltrace command
```

## File Permissions

### 1. Basic Permissions
```bash
# View permissions
ls -l file
stat file

# Modify permissions
chmod 644 file
chmod u=rw,g=r,o=r file

# Change owner
chown user:group file
```

### 2. Special Permissions
```bash
# Set special bits
chmod +s file      # SUID/SGID
chmod +t dir       # Sticky bit

# View special permissions
ls -la file
stat file
```

### 3. Access Control Lists
```bash
# View ACL
getfacl file

# Set ACL
setfacl -m u:user:rwx file
setfacl -m g:group:rx file

# Remove ACL
setfacl -x u:user file
```

## Security Considerations

### 1. SUID Management
```bash
# Find SUID files
find / -perm -4000 2>/dev/null

# Find SGID files
find / -perm -2000 2>/dev/null

# Find world-writable
find / -perm -2 2>/dev/null
```

### 2. Process Security
```bash
# Restrict capabilities
capsh --print
setcap cap_net_raw-ep file

# Sandbox execution
firejail program
chroot /path program
```

### 3. Access Control
```bash
# Mandatory Access Control
semanage fcontext -a -t type file
restorecon file

# AppArmor profiles
aa-status
aa-complain program
```

## System Monitoring

### 1. Resource Usage
```bash
# CPU usage
top
mpstat

# Memory usage
free -h
vmstat

# Disk usage
df -h
iostat
```

### 2. Process Activity
```bash
# Process accounting
lastcomm
acct

# System calls
strace -c command
ltrace -c command
```

### 3. Audit Logging
```bash
# View audit logs
ausearch -f file
aureport

# Configure auditing
auditctl -w file -p rwxa
autrace command
```

## Troubleshooting

### 1. Common Issues
- Permission denied
- Operation not permitted
- No such file
- Resource limits

### 2. Solutions
```bash
# Check permissions
ls -l file
namei -l /path/to/file

# Check capabilities
getcap file
capsh --print
```

### 3. Debugging
```bash
# System calls
strace command 2>&1 | less

# Library calls
ltrace command 2>&1 | less

# Process info
cat /proc/PID/status
```

## Best Practices

### 1. Security
- Minimize SUID usage
- Regular audits
- Proper permissions
- Process isolation

### 2. Performance
- Resource limits
- Process priority
- Memory management
- Disk I/O control

### 3. Maintenance
- Regular monitoring
- Log rotation
- Security updates
- Access review

